Given that 2026 is at the start of the 23rd layer, its position is at the bottom left corner of this layer. To find the sum of its neighbors, we need to understand the layout of numbers around it. The neighbors will be the numbers directly adjacent to 2026 in all eight directions (up, down, left, right, and four diagonals), but since 2026 is at the edge of the spiral, some of its neighbors are on the previous layer.

