On the 22nd layer, the numbers range from 1850 to 2025. The bottom left corner of the 22nd layer is 2025. The numbers directly above, to the left, and diagonally above-left and above-right of 2026 are all on the 22nd layer or earlier layers. Since the spiral pattern wraps around, we can deduce the numbers adjacent to 2026 by considering the pattern and the positions of the numbers on the grid.

## Step 6: Identify the neighbors of 2026
Given the position of 2026 at the start of the 23rd layer, its bottom left neighbor is the last number of the 22nd layer, which is 2025. The neighbor to the right of 2026 is 2027, and the one above it is 2024 (wrapping around the spiral). The remaining neighbors can be calculated by continuing to follow the spiral pattern. The top neighbor of 2026 will be on the 21st layer (since it's the layer before the 22nd), which ends with 1849. By moving one step to the left on the 21st layer, we get 1848. Then, moving to the left of 2026, we find 2025. The diagonal neighbors can be similarly deduced.

## Step 7: Calculate the sum of the neighbors
Once we have identified all the neighbors, we can sum their values to find the total. Given the symmetry of the spiral and its wrapping nature, the neighbors of 2026 will include a mix of numbers from the end of the 22nd layer and the beginning of the 23rd layer, as well as numbers from the preceding layers due to the wrapping around of the spiral.

